1 mate rial, as defined in Section 1024.1 of this title. In the case
2 of any unsolicited mailing of any of the material listed in this
3 section, the offense is deemed complete from the time such material
4 is deposited in any post office or delivered to any person with
5 intent that it shall be forwarded. Also, unless preempted by
6 federal law, no unsolicited mail which is harmful to minors pursuant
7 to Section 1040.75 of this title shall be mailed to any person. The
8 party mailing the materials specified in this section may be
9 indicted and tried in any county wherein such material is deposited
10 or delivered, or in which it is received by the person to whom it is
11 addressed.
12 B. Any person who violates any provision of this section
13 involving obscene materials, upon conviction, shall be guilty of a
14 misdemeanor felony and shall be punished by imprisonment in the
15 county jail custody of the Department of Corrections for not more
16 less than one (1) year and not more than three (3) years, or by a
17 fine of not less than Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00), or by both
18 such fine and imprisonment.
19 C. Any person who violates any provision of this section
20 involving child sexual abuse material, upon conviction, shall be
21 guilty of a felony and shall be punished by imprisonment in the
22 custody of the Department of Corrections for not less than three (3)
23 years and not more than twenty (20) years, or by a fine of not less
24 than Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), or by both such fine and
